A “diving bell” made of stainless steel, which is directly pressurized by a controlled gas flow, is used to maintain a stable liquid-gas interface between the gate and anode electrodes. It encloses the top PMT array. The height of the liquid level inside the bell is controlled via a vertically-adjustable gas-exhaust tube. Possible tilts of the TPC are measured by means of four custom-made parallel-plate-capacitive levelmeters installed inside the diving bell. They cover a dynamic range of 10 mm and have a precision of ∼\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
