Illustration of the XENON1T DAQ system for the TPC and the muon veto. The two detectors are time-synchronized. The acquisition monitor consists of one high-data bandwidth ADC which records the sum of all bottom array PMTs and selected digital information, even when the other ADCs are busy or vetoed

The TPC DAQ is trigger-less in the sense that every pulse above a ∼\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
