Due to the lower drift field compared to the initial design, boundary effects to the field become relatively more important, especially close to the TPC walls and close to the cathode. The field lines at large radii are no longer straight but bend toward smaller radii (see Fig. 3). This leads to an inward-bias of the reconstructed event positions but ensures that no charge signal is lost. An (R, Z)-dependent field correction map was constructed using an axisymmetric 3D finite element simulation of the realized geometry. The map was verified by means of calibration data (83m\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
